                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760c.61/259: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-27T18:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 29—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>468. Consul at Danzig telegraphs 25th that as a result of energetic measures
                    taken by Great Britain and France ammunition for Poland is now being forwarded
                    to its destination by the Free City. Naval forces have been reinforced and
                    everything quiet. Some of ammunition being unloaded by Danzig laborers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
